    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="414"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d414">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.00/2042⅝</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Adviser on Political Relations</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Murray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to Admiral <persName type="to">William D.
                            Leahy</persName>, Chief of Staff to the Commander in Chief of the Army
                        and Navy</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-16">October 16,
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to Mr. Berle’s letter of October 15, regarding the situation in Iran,
                    there is attached a copy of Mr. Hull’s letter to the President of August 16,
                        1943,<note n="32" xml:id="d414fn32">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_377">p. 377</ref>.</note>
                    mentioned in Mr. Berle’s letter.</p>
                <p>There is also enclosed a copy of a memorandum of January 23, 1943,<note n="33"
                        xml:id="d414fn33">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_331">p. 331</ref>.</note>
                    which explains the basis of the State Department’s policy toward Iran.
                    Subsequent events in Iran have only confirmed our view that the policy outlined
                    will best serve American interests in that area.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wallace Murray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
